comments.body:
Since iteration could misbehave severely and this would pass (e.g. if `Next()` would return `nullptr` we wouldn't even enter the loop), it could make more sense to iterate over the target nodes instead, something like:
```C++
    auto node{head.second.Next()};
    for (const auto& expected : nodes) {
        BOOST_CHECK_EQUAL(&expected, node);
        node = node->second.Next();
    }
    BOOST_CHECK_EQUAL(nullptr, node);
```
or
```C++
    auto node{&head};
    for (const auto& expected : nodes) {
        node = node->second.Next();
        BOOST_CHECK_EQUAL(&expected, node);
    }
    BOOST_CHECK_EQUAL(node->second.Next(), nullptr);
```

